io.flutter.plugin.common

Interface MethodCodec

  • All Known Implementing Classes:
    JSONMethodCodec, StandardMethodCodec

    public interface MethodCodec
    A codec for method calls and enveloped results. Method calls are encoded as binary messages with enough structure that the codec can extract a method name String and an arguments Object. These data items are used to populate a MethodCall. All operations throw IllegalArgumentException, if conversion fails.
